## Section 3: Threat Actors ##\

- Threat Actors:
    - Individuals or entities that are responsible for incidents impacting security of an organization. Categorized into the following 5 types:
        - Unskilled Attackers
        - Hacktivists
        - Organized Crime
        - Nation State Actors
        - Insider Threats
    - Motivations of Threat Actors are categorized under the following groups:
        - Data Exfil
        - Blackmail
        - Philosophical / Political Beliefs
        - Ethical Reasons
        - Espionage
        - Revenge
        - Service Disruption
        - Disruption or Chaos
        - Financial Gain 
        - War